WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:32.031 --> 00:36.102
- This world is seething
with crime and corruption,

00:36.169 --> 00:39.806
and we are
its angels of mercy.

00:39.873 --> 00:45.044
Junior Deputies, take it in
with all its twisted majesty.

00:45.111 --> 00:49.182
{\an1}- Oh, wow, a rainbow.
What a delight.

00:49.249 --> 00:52.452
- On our patrols, it is our duty
to help those in need

00:52.519 --> 00:55.488
{\an3}and stop bad guys
from breaking the law.

00:55.555 --> 00:57.924
- Harvey and I wanna know, when
do we get our own Ba-Zappers?

00:57.991 --> 01:00.260
{\an3}- You're not getting a laser,
Dade.

01:00.326 --> 01:01.694
- [giggling] Hey, Harvey.
- [screams]

01:01.761 --> 01:03.396
- [giggling]
It's just us.

01:03.463 --> 01:04.596
- You two are kooky.

01:04.664 --> 01:06.266
- Nice body-napkin.
So what?

01:06.332 --> 01:08.535
You're one
of those Junior Squealers now?

01:08.601 --> 01:10.970
- Oh, Fee,
we're called Junior Deputies,

01:11.037 --> 01:12.372
not Junior Squealers.

01:12.439 --> 01:14.541
{\an3}- Deputies!
A citizen in need!

01:14.607 --> 01:17.544
{\an3}- Don't worry.
Help is on the way.

01:17.610 --> 01:20.547
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:20.613 --> 01:27.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:27.420 --> 01:30.323
- Help! Help!
My kite's stuck in a tree.

01:30.390 --> 01:31.524
- Don't worry,
innocent youth,

01:31.591 --> 01:34.093
{\an3}we have the situation
under control.

01:34.160 --> 01:36.362
[panicked chatter]

01:36.429 --> 01:39.599
- Got it.
Here you go, Citizen Pip.

01:39.666 --> 01:41.534
- Wow, you're my heroes.

01:41.601 --> 01:45.538
- Good job, Deputies.
We've won this battle.

01:45.605 --> 01:47.173
{\an3}- Hey, guys,
look over there.

01:47.240 --> 01:50.143
{\an3}The library has
a giant mustache.

01:50.210 --> 01:54.147
- Ah! Over there too!
Ira Fingerman has a mustache.

01:54.214 --> 01:57.750
- Hey, there's even one
on Moff's mailbox.

01:57.817 --> 02:00.220
- [gasps]
Vandalism.

02:00.286 --> 02:03.423
Everybody back.
This is a crime scene.

02:03.490 --> 02:05.959
- But these mustaches
are so harmless.

02:06.025 --> 02:07.260
- Harmless?

02:07.327 --> 02:10.497
Defacing property is
a serious offense.

02:10.562 --> 02:12.799
- Oh, wow.
It's written on parchment.

02:12.866 --> 02:14.100
This is serious.

02:14.167 --> 02:16.402
- Now, now,
don't mind, officers.

02:16.469 --> 02:19.305
I've been away for two days.
I just want to check the mail.

02:19.372 --> 02:23.643
Oh, it's still empty.
Carry on.

02:23.710 --> 02:27.814
- All right, Deputies.
We have a criminal at large.

02:27.881 --> 02:29.816
We're looking
for a real pro,

02:29.883 --> 02:33.019
someone with a history
of mischief.

02:33.086 --> 02:34.721
- [gasps]
Fee!

02:34.787 --> 02:39.158
- Based on the dirty footprints,
the perp is someone this tall.

02:39.225 --> 02:41.194
- Hey, guys, check out
this weird paint I found

02:41.261 --> 02:42.529
behind Moff's place.

02:42.595 --> 02:45.164
It grows plants
when you smear it on stuff.

02:45.231 --> 02:46.633
{\an3}- Fee, we don't have time
for this.

02:46.699 --> 02:48.501
We're in the middle
of an investigation.

02:48.568 --> 02:51.538
- The culprit has a crude
yet whimsical hand.

02:51.604 --> 02:55.375
Be on the lookout for anyone
with a large brush.

02:55.441 --> 02:56.543
- Hey, Fee.

02:56.609 --> 02:59.012
{\an1}Officer Fredd,
who could've done this?

02:59.078 --> 03:01.281
{\an1}- I don't know,
but whoever they are,

03:01.347 --> 03:02.615
they're in big trouble.

03:02.682 --> 03:06.185
{\an3}- Uh, maybe we can just
give them a warning?

03:06.252 --> 03:07.754
It's such a small crime.

03:07.820 --> 03:09.255
- Oh, Harvey.

03:09.322 --> 03:12.492
It is the small crimes
that are the most insidious.

03:12.559 --> 03:14.460
It's called a gateway crime.

03:14.527 --> 03:17.530
It'll lead to bigger crimes
and bigger crimes,

03:17.597 --> 03:20.266
and eventually--

03:20.333 --> 03:23.136
- Oh, no.
- [laughs nervously]

03:23.202 --> 03:26.973
- All right, split into pairs,
and find this criminal.

03:27.040 --> 03:29.876
{\an3}- Harvey and I will team up.
We got this.

03:29.943 --> 03:33.313
{\an3}Whoever's doing these mustaches
is a real sicko.

03:33.379 --> 03:36.316
{\an3}Yeah, when we find them, we're
gonna put him away for good.

03:36.382 --> 03:38.751
{\an1}- Uh, Dade, can I talk to you
about something?

03:38.818 --> 03:41.654
{\an1}Let's say you know someone
who's in trouble,

03:41.721 --> 03:43.156
but they're your friend--

03:43.222 --> 03:45.592
{\an3}- [gasps] Harvey,
no matter what you've done,

03:45.658 --> 03:48.227
you know I've always
got your back, buddy.

03:48.294 --> 03:49.963
{\an1}- No, Dade,
I didn't leave the must--

03:50.029 --> 03:53.566
{\an3}- And even if my back is turned,
I'm still looking out for you.

03:53.633 --> 03:55.835
- I think
Fee's drawing the mustaches.

03:55.902 --> 03:58.338
- What? Quick, you gotta tell
Officer Fredd.

03:58.404 --> 04:00.974
- No!
- But, Harvey, oh, why?

04:01.040 --> 04:03.042
You're not making sense.

04:03.109 --> 04:04.744
- Fee's my friend.

04:04.811 --> 04:07.180
She needs someone to show her
that what she's doing is wrong.

04:07.246 --> 04:10.550
I'd do the same for you.
Will you help me, please?

04:10.617 --> 04:13.119
- Ugh, all right.
What's your plan?

04:13.186 --> 04:15.188
<i>[playful music]</i>

04:15.254 --> 04:18.156
- [babbles]
"I'm a big, dumb mountain."

04:18.224 --> 04:19.858
[babbles]

04:19.926 --> 04:21.461
[chuckles]
I'm funny.

04:21.527 --> 04:24.330
- Oh, uh, hey there, Fee.
[chuckles]

04:24.397 --> 04:27.333
- Oh, hey, Harvey.
- Yeah, right on.

04:27.400 --> 04:30.737
{\an1}I've, uh, seen a lot
of these mustaches around town.

04:30.803 --> 04:34.540
{\an1}Whoever's doing them is gonna be
in pretty big trouble.

04:34.607 --> 04:37.243
{\an3}- Why are you talking
like an old person?

04:37.310 --> 04:42.215
{\an1}- So, uh, I heard there's, like,
a play going on

04:42.281 --> 04:43.616
or something around here.

04:43.683 --> 04:45.318
You wanna check it out?

04:45.385 --> 04:48.021
{\an3}- Ugh, is this
a Junior Squealers thing?

04:48.087 --> 04:50.790
- [chuckles]

04:50.857 --> 04:52.225
- Where's everyone else?

04:52.291 --> 04:55.428
{\an3}- Oh, whoa, whoa,
I think it's starting.

04:55.495 --> 04:57.697
- I'm vandalizing property,

04:57.764 --> 05:00.967
and I don't care
how it affects my life.

05:01.034 --> 05:02.035
- [imitates police siren]

05:02.101 --> 05:04.037
- Oh, no, I'm getting arrested,

05:04.103 --> 05:06.806
and now I'm in jail.

05:06.873 --> 05:08.941
Oh, no!
Why?

05:09.008 --> 05:10.343
{\an1}- Hmm.

05:10.410 --> 05:12.545
- Gasp, who's there?

05:12.612 --> 05:13.880
- [snapping]

05:13.946 --> 05:15.381
- Hardened criminals.

05:15.448 --> 05:18.951
- Society just pushed me,
and then I snapped.

05:19.018 --> 05:21.020
Now I'm a psycho!

05:21.087 --> 05:23.556
- And I have
an evil eye patch.

05:23.623 --> 05:26.492
{\an3}- I eat stickers.
You like that?

05:26.559 --> 05:27.727
- Ugh!

05:27.794 --> 05:30.863
{\an3}- Wow, pretty scary, huh?
And eye-opening.

05:30.930 --> 05:34.267
- You did the crime.
- Now serve the time.

05:34.333 --> 05:37.370
- Serve the time?
How much time?

05:37.437 --> 05:39.639
all: Forever and ever.

05:39.706 --> 05:45.178
♪ We ruined our lives,
and now we're trapped forever ♪

05:45.244 --> 05:48.014
So remember,
don't break the law,

05:48.081 --> 05:50.349
or else you'll ruin your life.

05:50.416 --> 05:53.786
all: ♪ Forever ♪

05:53.853 --> 05:55.354
[all breathing heavily]

05:55.421 --> 05:58.224
{\an3}- So, um, what'd you think
of the message there?

05:58.291 --> 06:01.728
- Wow, that was...

06:01.794 --> 06:03.029
hilarious!

06:03.096 --> 06:05.231
[laughing]

06:05.298 --> 06:06.866
{\an3}- [laughs]
Thanks, Fee.

06:06.933 --> 06:09.569
- No, Claire,
it's not supposed to be funny.

06:09.635 --> 06:11.537
{\an1}- Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
Guys, guys, guys.

06:11.604 --> 06:14.774
{\an1}What was this?
What was this move?

06:14.841 --> 06:16.375
- It's a dance!

06:16.442 --> 06:19.112
{\an3}- But didn't the play teach you
anything about the law?

06:19.178 --> 06:20.780
- Um, yeah.

06:20.847 --> 06:23.516
It taught me if I'm gonna get in
trouble and locked up for life,

06:23.583 --> 06:27.553
{\an1}I better make it count
and go down in a blaze of glory.

06:27.620 --> 06:30.456
{\an1}Hey, I gotta run.
I suddenly feel inspired.

06:30.523 --> 06:32.759
- Wait, that's not the lesson.

06:32.825 --> 06:36.696
{\an1}- Well, that was fun, but we
better get back to patrolling.

06:36.763 --> 06:39.198
{\an3}- Yeah, the mustache marauder
is still out there.

06:39.265 --> 06:43.136
- Harvey, it didn't work,
and we gave it our all up here.

06:43.202 --> 06:45.538
- Uh, I can't get through
to her,

06:45.605 --> 06:48.741
but maybe I can still keep her
from getting busted.

06:48.808 --> 06:51.744
<i>[mischievous music]</i>

06:51.811 --> 06:53.946
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:54.013 --> 06:57.350
[grunting]

06:57.416 --> 06:58.951
- Freeze!
- [gasps]

06:59.018 --> 07:02.588
{\an3}- The criminal always returns
to the scene of the crime.

07:02.655 --> 07:04.657
{\an1}- Harvey, you're the one
drawing these?

07:04.724 --> 07:06.726
- Wait, this isn't
what it looks like.

07:06.793 --> 07:09.061
- Lies! Betrayal!

07:09.128 --> 07:11.197
This calls for double ba-zaps.

07:11.264 --> 07:12.398
- Wait, Officer Fredd.

07:12.465 --> 07:14.367
{\an1}Harvey is innocent.
It's Fee.

07:14.433 --> 07:16.068
She's been drawing
all the mustaches.

07:16.135 --> 07:17.236
{\an3}- Dade!

07:17.303 --> 07:19.872
- You knew
Fee was behind this,

07:19.939 --> 07:21.274
and you hid it from us?

07:21.340 --> 07:22.775
{\an3}- Yeah, I was just trying
to save her

07:22.842 --> 07:24.477
from going down
the wrong path.

07:24.544 --> 07:27.146
{\an3}- Your judgment
has been compromised.

07:27.213 --> 07:29.048
{\an3}Hand over
your deputy sash.

07:29.115 --> 07:30.316
[both gasp]

07:30.383 --> 07:33.286
- Harvey, no.
- Aw, he's right.

07:33.352 --> 07:35.288
{\an3}I don't deserve
to wear this.

07:35.354 --> 07:38.124
{\an3}- Junior Deputies,
let's roll out.

07:38.191 --> 07:39.926
{\an3}We have to catch
that girl.

07:39.992 --> 07:41.427
- Uh, I'm so sorry.

07:41.494 --> 07:43.462
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

07:43.529 --> 07:45.698
- Ugh, what have I done?

07:45.765 --> 07:47.433
{\an3}- Ah, maybe the mail
has arrived and--

07:47.500 --> 07:50.736
{\an3}oh, okay,
still no mail, all right.

07:52.271 --> 07:53.573
- Oh, sweetie, I'm sorry

07:53.639 --> 07:55.708
{\an3}the Junior Deputy thing
didn't work out.

07:55.775 --> 07:57.944
{\an3}And, you know,
I get where Fee is coming from.

07:58.010 --> 08:00.279
{\an3}I've had my run-ins
with the law.

08:00.346 --> 08:02.281
It can be addictive.

08:02.348 --> 08:05.451
- I tried to be a good friend
and a good Junior Deputy,

08:05.518 --> 08:06.919
and I failed at both.

08:06.986 --> 08:09.155
{\an3}- You know, as long as you
follow your heart,

08:09.222 --> 08:10.923
you're never a failure.

08:10.990 --> 08:14.493
- My heart's telling me that
I can still save my friends.

08:14.560 --> 08:16.963
{\an3}- Then you get out there,
sweetie.

08:17.029 --> 08:19.966
- Thanks, Mom.
- I'm a good mom.

08:20.032 --> 08:22.668
[panting]

08:22.735 --> 08:25.238
- Okay, if I were
a fugitive on the run,

08:25.304 --> 08:27.874
where would I be--
oh, there they are.

08:27.940 --> 08:29.308
- Hey, Harvey.

08:29.375 --> 08:30.877
{\an3}Dude, you're just in time
for something huge.

08:30.943 --> 08:34.280
{\an1}I'm gonna paint a mustache
on that mountain.

08:34.347 --> 08:35.280
- And I'm gonna help.

08:35.347 --> 08:38.049
- This will be my legacy.

08:38.116 --> 08:40.785
<i>For eons to come,</i>
<i>people will stare in awe</i>

08:40.852 --> 08:41.988
<i>and whisper...</i>

08:42.054 --> 08:44.490
{\an1}- Uh, I think that mountain
has a mustache.

08:44.557 --> 08:45.691
<i>[magical chimes]</i>

08:45.758 --> 08:47.360
- Mwahahahahaha.

08:47.426 --> 08:49.829
{\an1}Anyway, you should come.
It'll be so fun.

08:49.896 --> 08:51.731
- Guys, you need
to stop this.

08:51.797 --> 08:53.432
Turn yourselves in
before it's too--

08:53.499 --> 08:56.335
- Too late.
We have you surrounded.

08:56.402 --> 08:59.205
{\an1}- Harvey, look, Officer Fredd
gave us all lasers.

08:59.272 --> 09:01.107
{\an1}Ba-zap, ba-zap!
Ba-zap!

09:01.173 --> 09:02.441
- Ba-zap! Ba-zap!

09:02.508 --> 09:04.644
- I think mine's broke.
[screams]

09:04.710 --> 09:05.845
Ouch.

09:05.912 --> 09:08.547
{\an1}- Harvey, good job
leading us right to them.

09:08.614 --> 09:10.383
Welcome back to the force.

09:10.449 --> 09:12.084
- Oh, no.
What have I done?

09:12.151 --> 09:15.454
- You'll never take us alive!
[laughs sinisterly]

09:15.521 --> 09:17.023
- After them!

09:17.089 --> 09:19.191
- A-whoo!
- Come on!

09:19.258 --> 09:20.226
[both grunt]

09:20.293 --> 09:22.428
- Oh, that's too far.

09:22.495 --> 09:25.498
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:25.564 --> 09:27.600
[laser shoots]
- Ba-zap!

09:27.667 --> 09:28.768
- Oh, that's poison sumac.

09:28.834 --> 09:30.102
{\an1}If I touch it,
my rash will come back.

09:30.169 --> 09:31.437
Harvey, I'm sorry!

09:31.504 --> 09:34.307
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:34.373 --> 09:35.975
- [laughs]

09:36.042 --> 09:37.009
- A-bazap!

09:37.076 --> 09:40.279
- Ah!
My brush.

09:40.346 --> 09:41.981
{\an1}- You go!
I'll stall them.

09:42.048 --> 09:44.717
Ah-yayayayaya!

09:44.784 --> 09:46.285
- Ah!

09:46.352 --> 09:48.688
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:48.754 --> 09:50.957
{\an1}- Fee, stop.
I'm trying to help you.

09:51.023 --> 09:53.592
{\an3}- If you want to help,
then grab one of these brushes.

09:53.659 --> 09:55.695
- I can't.
It's against the law.

09:55.761 --> 09:57.096
It's not worth it, Fee.

09:57.163 --> 09:58.731
- I'm almost there.

09:58.798 --> 10:02.568
- Ever since two days ago,
it's been my lifelong dream

10:02.635 --> 10:04.770
to draw a mustache
on this mountain.

10:04.837 --> 10:06.639
If you want to stand in my way
like everybody else,

10:06.706 --> 10:07.940
that's fine.

10:08.007 --> 10:10.242
I just thought
you'd be on my side.

10:10.309 --> 10:13.512
- I-I am on your side.

10:13.579 --> 10:17.717
{\an3}- I'm doing this
with or without you.

10:17.783 --> 10:18.985
Mm, uh--

10:19.051 --> 10:20.886
- Only two more rungs.

10:20.953 --> 10:23.456
{\an1}I love counting rungs
on ladders.

10:23.522 --> 10:27.593
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:27.660 --> 10:29.362
{\an1}Ah!

10:29.428 --> 10:31.297
- Mm, I'm sorry!

10:31.364 --> 10:33.065
- What? Harvey?

10:33.132 --> 10:35.735
- Let's do this.

10:35.801 --> 10:41.474
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:41.540 --> 10:46.078
- Whoa.
- They did it!

10:46.145 --> 10:48.581
{\an1}- We're gonna be
in so much trouble.

10:48.647 --> 10:51.150
- Yeah, but it was worth it.

10:51.217 --> 10:53.052
{\an1}- Double ba-zap!
That's it.

10:53.119 --> 10:56.622
{\an1}I'm punishing both of you to
the fullest extent of the law.

10:58.424 --> 10:59.658
{\an1}All right,
your ten minutes are up.

10:59.725 --> 11:00.960
You're free to go.

11:01.027 --> 11:04.630
{\an1}I hope you two
learned a lesson from all this.

11:04.697 --> 11:06.832
- Oh, I sure did.
I learned that--

11:06.899 --> 11:09.735
- Let's go smash stuff!
- Okay!

11:09.802 --> 11:11.070
- Yeah!

11:11.137 --> 11:13.139
[all laughing]

11:17.309 --> 11:19.145
<i>Harvey: There's nothing better</i>
<i>than a home</i>

11:19.211 --> 11:21.981
<i>to keep you safe</i>
<i>from the world outside.</i>

11:22.048 --> 11:25.618
<i>It keeps you warm,</i>
<i>thankful, and happy.</i>

11:25.684 --> 11:27.119
[yawns]

11:27.186 --> 11:28.721
<i>Because it's</i>
<i>your own little place</i>

11:28.788 --> 11:30.923
<i>with all the things you need.</i>

11:30.990 --> 11:33.592
<i>Without a home,</i>
<i>you'd be lost.</i>

11:33.659 --> 11:35.661
<i>Where would you go at night?</i>

11:35.728 --> 11:38.364
<i>Where would you put</i>
<i>your things?</i>

11:38.431 --> 11:39.532
<i>Who would take care of you?</i>

11:39.598 --> 11:41.333
[teeth chattering]

11:41.400 --> 11:42.701
<i>Everybody needs a home.</i>

11:42.768 --> 11:43.736
[thunder]

11:43.803 --> 11:46.205
Ah! Fee and Foo!

11:46.272 --> 11:49.208
<i>[ominous music]</i>

11:49.275 --> 11:57.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:59.051 --> 12:01.620
Foo! Fee!
Where are you guys?

12:01.687 --> 12:03.255
- Up here, dude.

12:03.322 --> 12:04.623
both: Hey!

12:04.690 --> 12:06.459
- Oh, my gosh!
Are you all right?

12:06.525 --> 12:07.960
{\an1}- Sure.
Why wouldn't we be?

12:08.027 --> 12:09.795
{\an3}- Uh-oh,
I'm losing my grip.

12:09.862 --> 12:12.098
- Uh-oh, so am I.

12:12.164 --> 12:13.365
- Uh-oh.
- Uh-oh.

12:13.432 --> 12:14.700
[both scream]

12:14.767 --> 12:16.402
[laughing]

12:16.469 --> 12:19.205
- Okay, you really shouldn't
be out in a storm like this.

12:19.271 --> 12:20.539
It isn't safe.

12:20.606 --> 12:22.074
I think you need
a real home.

12:22.141 --> 12:24.043
I want you
to move in with me.

12:24.110 --> 12:26.846
{\an1}- Aww, thanks, dude,
but we're fine.

12:26.912 --> 12:29.215
{\an3}- Yeah, I love it
out here.

12:33.085 --> 12:35.855
- Don't you get sick of getting
rained on all the time?

12:35.921 --> 12:38.691
I mean, look at you.
You're soaked.

12:38.757 --> 12:41.026
- Achoo.
- Achoo.

12:41.093 --> 12:42.628
[laughing]

12:42.695 --> 12:44.497
- Well, it doesn't have
to be like that.

12:44.563 --> 12:47.766
{\an1}If you lived at my house,
you'd be warm and dry right now.

12:47.833 --> 12:49.001
{\an3}both: Ooh.

12:49.068 --> 12:50.336
- You'll have
your own beds.

12:50.402 --> 12:52.404
You'll get
three healthy meals a day.

12:52.471 --> 12:55.074
Oh, and yeah,
there's something else at home--

12:55.141 --> 12:57.343
I bet it will blow
your mind.

12:57.409 --> 12:59.011
[clears throat]

12:59.078 --> 13:02.214
♪ Out here in the trees
you can do as you please ♪

13:02.281 --> 13:06.118
♪ Mother Nature
is your provider ♪

13:06.185 --> 13:07.786
♪ You might think
it's bliss ♪

13:07.853 --> 13:09.688
♪ But there's one thing
you've missed ♪

13:09.755 --> 13:12.892
♪ And that, my friends,
is hot cider ♪

13:12.958 --> 13:15.694
♪ Hot cider ♪

13:15.761 --> 13:17.730
{\an1}- Cider?
What's cider?

13:17.796 --> 13:19.798
- Only the best drink ever.

13:19.865 --> 13:21.834
{\an3}It feels like
you're drinking a hug,

13:21.901 --> 13:24.703
{\an3}and you can only get it
in a house.

13:24.770 --> 13:28.107
♪ So move in with me
and my family ♪

13:28.174 --> 13:31.610
♪ Not just
for an overnighter ♪

13:31.677 --> 13:35.247
♪ We'll sit by the fire,
you'll get warmer and drier ♪

13:35.314 --> 13:38.617
♪ And mom will make us
hot cider ♪

13:38.684 --> 13:42.254
♪ We can eat lots of stuff,
there's always enough ♪

13:42.321 --> 13:45.591
♪ Food you can put
inside ya ♪

13:45.658 --> 13:49.361
♪ Nights don't seem so long,
nothing goes wrong ♪

13:49.428 --> 13:52.731
♪ As long as you've got
hot cider ♪

13:52.798 --> 13:54.700
♪ Hot cider ♪

13:54.767 --> 13:56.602
Come on.
- Okay!

13:56.669 --> 13:58.204
both: ♪ Cider ♪

13:58.270 --> 13:59.939
- It does sound
pretty good.

14:00.005 --> 14:03.242
{\an1}- ♪ So follow me down
to the middle of town ♪

14:03.309 --> 14:06.946
{\an1}♪ When you're dry,
you'll feel much lighter ♪

14:07.012 --> 14:12.318
♪ You don't need a lot
as long as you've got ♪

14:12.384 --> 14:18.824
{\an1}♪ Four walls, a roof,
and hot cider ♪

14:18.891 --> 14:20.759
- Did you just
make that song up?

14:20.826 --> 14:23.963
{\an3}- Wait, how did we
get here?

14:24.029 --> 14:26.899
{\an8}<i>- And now,</i>
<i>back to our KBRK matinee.</i>

14:26.966 --> 14:29.401
{\an3}- Gee, I wonder
where the monster is.

14:29.468 --> 14:30.502
- I don't know.

14:30.569 --> 14:32.571
{\an1}Let's just keep
walking out here.

14:32.638 --> 14:34.340
- [growling]

14:34.406 --> 14:37.910
{\an3}- Oh! No, no! Girls, girls,
the monster's right behind you.

14:37.977 --> 14:40.546
Please, just turn around.
- Honey, get a grip.

14:40.613 --> 14:42.314
- Mom, Dad.
- [yelps]

14:42.381 --> 14:45.384
- Kids, you're soaked!
I'll get some towels.

14:45.451 --> 14:48.287
- I don't think Fee and Foo
should live in a tree anymore.

14:48.354 --> 14:51.257
Eh!
So can they please live with us?

14:51.323 --> 14:53.726
- You kids have been living
in a tree this whole time?

14:53.792 --> 14:56.428
- It's more like
on top of a tree.

14:56.495 --> 14:57.763
- Oh, my gosh.

14:57.830 --> 14:59.798
- Well, of course you can live
with us, kids.

14:59.865 --> 15:03.068
We've got an empty guest room
that should fit you just right.

15:03.135 --> 15:05.104
And one more thing--

15:05.170 --> 15:08.240
some apple cider
should warm you up.

15:08.307 --> 15:09.708
- You guys are gonna
love this.

15:09.775 --> 15:11.477
[both sipping]

15:11.543 --> 15:13.512
- Whoa.
- Right?

15:13.579 --> 15:18.284
{\an3}- Harvey, I want to drink this
all day for the rest of my life.

15:18.350 --> 15:20.853
- So here it is,
your new room.

15:20.919 --> 15:23.489
I made you guys
personalized beds.

15:23.555 --> 15:24.690
{\an1}- Awesome!

15:24.757 --> 15:27.893
[laughter]

15:28.794 --> 15:30.062
- Whoa, yeah!

15:30.129 --> 15:31.430
- And here's another thing.

15:31.497 --> 15:33.432
You guys have
your own closet now.

15:33.499 --> 15:34.833
- Cool, what for?

15:34.900 --> 15:36.969
- In case you ever get
any more clothes.

15:37.036 --> 15:40.439
{\an1}Man, you guys,
this is gonna be great.

15:40.506 --> 15:42.708
{\an1}We're gonna have so much fun
now that we're safe

15:42.775 --> 15:44.843
{\an1}from the wind
and the rain out there.

15:44.910 --> 15:47.446
So what do you want
to do first?

15:47.513 --> 15:50.449
[laughter]

15:52.217 --> 15:55.120
Uh, guys,
I'm getting pretty soggy.

15:55.187 --> 15:56.955
I think I'm gonna
go back inside.

15:57.022 --> 15:58.490
- That's cool, dude.

15:58.557 --> 16:00.225
Me and Foo are gonna stay
out here a little longer.

16:00.292 --> 16:01.527
Ah!
You little--

16:01.593 --> 16:02.895
[splashing and laughing]

16:02.961 --> 16:04.163
- Well, just make sure
you're back

16:04.229 --> 16:05.431
in time for dinner.

16:07.066 --> 16:09.535
[humming]

16:09.601 --> 16:13.906
Okay, Sis, now I'm thinking
a tree should be purple.

16:13.972 --> 16:17.076
<i>- All right, kids,</i>
<i>time for dinner.</i>

16:17.142 --> 16:19.878
- Fee! Foo!
Dinnertime!

16:22.281 --> 16:24.717
Hmm, maybe they can't
hear the bell.

16:24.783 --> 16:25.918
Better keep ringing it.

16:25.984 --> 16:28.954
[clanking metal]

16:35.494 --> 16:40.199
{\an3}- Harvey, down here.
Nice bell.

16:40.265 --> 16:43.001
- Oh, guys.
You must have not heard me.

16:43.068 --> 16:46.805
Better ring the bell harder
next time.

16:46.872 --> 16:48.273
- What's the bell for?

16:48.340 --> 16:49.842
- It's to let you know
to come home.

16:49.908 --> 16:53.212
{\an3}- Well, we can't.
We aren't done with the mud yet.

16:54.279 --> 16:56.515
Now we're done.

16:58.951 --> 17:01.487
{\an3}- Let's get washed
before we go down for dinner.

17:01.553 --> 17:02.287
- Dinner!

17:02.354 --> 17:03.822
- Foo!
[thud]

17:03.889 --> 17:06.858
We gotta get all that dirt
off you before we go eat.

17:06.925 --> 17:08.827
- What dirt?
I ain't dirty.

17:08.894 --> 17:12.064
- Let's play a game called
"the wash 'em up" game.

17:12.131 --> 17:14.566
- Okay, I'm gonna wash myself
so good.

17:14.633 --> 17:18.069
- I'm the best washer.
[laughter]

17:18.137 --> 17:22.708
- Hey, Harvey,
watch me wash.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.643
Wash, wash--
whoa!

17:24.710 --> 17:28.180
- Wash, wash.
- Harvey, wash, wash!

17:28.247 --> 17:31.950
- Uh, that's not
how you play.

17:32.818 --> 17:35.053
{\an1}- A-achoo!

17:35.120 --> 17:37.322
- Welcome to dinnertime,
where we eat

17:37.389 --> 17:40.058
delicious meals together
as a family.

17:40.125 --> 17:41.527
I love you so much, Mom.

17:41.593 --> 17:42.694
- Thanks, Harvey.

17:42.761 --> 17:44.062
Now eat up, kids.

17:44.129 --> 17:46.365
[Fee and Foo gobbling]

17:46.432 --> 17:47.966
both: Thank you.

17:48.033 --> 17:51.103
both: Wash, wash, wash, wash,
wash, wash, wash, wash, wash.

17:52.805 --> 17:56.241
{\an1}- Guys, pay attention.
This is the best show ever.

17:56.308 --> 17:59.578
<i>- On today's episode of</i>
<i>"The Little TroubleMakerz,"</i>

17:59.645 --> 18:02.181
<i>the gang volunteers</i>
<i>at a retirement community.</i>

18:02.247 --> 18:04.049
<i>- Sorry we didn't</i>
<i>get you anything</i>

18:04.116 --> 18:05.984
<i>for your birthday,</i>
<i>Anabelle.</i>

18:06.051 --> 18:07.319
<i>all: Psych!</i>

18:07.386 --> 18:09.922
<i>- We brought you your grandson.</i>

18:09.988 --> 18:11.390
<i>- Hey, Nana.</i>

18:11.457 --> 18:15.561
<i>- Oh, you little troublemakerz!</i>
<i>[chuckles]</i>

18:15.627 --> 18:17.362
- Classic troublemaking.

18:17.429 --> 18:19.531
[laughter]

18:19.598 --> 18:22.534
Hey, guys, can you please
sit down and watch the show?

18:22.601 --> 18:23.836
both: Sorry, Harvey.

18:23.902 --> 18:28.607
<i>- Does anyone have B6?</i>
<i>B6, anybody have B6?</i>

18:28.674 --> 18:30.642
[laughing]

18:30.709 --> 18:33.545
- Guys, you're blocking
the screen.

18:33.612 --> 18:35.380
both: Sorry, Harvey.

18:35.447 --> 18:38.383
[laughter]

18:40.719 --> 18:42.254
[both snoring]

18:42.321 --> 18:45.090
{\an3}- Mom, Dad,
I've got a big old problem,

18:45.157 --> 18:46.458
and I need some advice.

18:46.525 --> 18:50.195
{\an1}- Harvey, farts just happen.
They're natural.

18:50.262 --> 18:51.930
{\an9}- No, it's not that
this time.

18:51.997 --> 18:54.666
{\an3}It's Fee and Foo.
They won't settle down.

18:54.733 --> 18:57.870
- Harvey, my father
once told me,

18:57.936 --> 19:00.506
"You do you.
I'll do me."

19:00.572 --> 19:03.442
Then he'd say,
"Now stop crying, boy!"

19:03.509 --> 19:05.277
[chuckles]
Dad was quite a character.

19:05.344 --> 19:08.247
Just do you, buddy,
and let Fee and Foo

19:08.313 --> 19:10.816
adjust at their own pace.

19:10.883 --> 19:12.017
Now go to bed.

19:12.084 --> 19:15.220
<i>[muffled laughter]</i>

19:17.122 --> 19:18.924
- Ugh, I can't take it.

19:18.991 --> 19:21.860
Fee and Foo need to learn
how to live in a home.

19:21.927 --> 19:24.162
<i>[muffled laughter]</i>

19:25.264 --> 19:27.366
Quit horsing around!

19:27.432 --> 19:28.500
{\an3}- Huh?

19:28.567 --> 19:31.303
- We were supposed to be
in bed at 7:30.

19:31.370 --> 19:33.238
It's 7:45!

19:33.305 --> 19:35.140
- Harvey, we usually
just fall asleep

19:35.207 --> 19:37.042
wherever our bodies collapse.

19:37.109 --> 19:38.710
- It doesn't work like that.

19:38.777 --> 19:41.179
- Well, then maybe
we need to leave.

19:41.246 --> 19:44.149
- No, I won't let you!
It's not safe.

19:44.216 --> 19:47.419
- Harvey, move out of my way.
- Never!

19:47.486 --> 19:50.556
- Harvey!
Quit being a dingus.

19:50.622 --> 19:54.493
- It's for your own good.
Now just go to sleep.

19:54.560 --> 19:57.563
Wait, did that
actually work?

19:57.629 --> 20:01.133
Fee? Foo?

20:01.199 --> 20:02.067
<i>[menacing music]</i>

20:02.134 --> 20:03.135
[thunder]

20:03.201 --> 20:04.136
[screams]

20:04.202 --> 20:10.175
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:10.242 --> 20:11.743
[thunder]

20:11.810 --> 20:14.846
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:14.913 --> 20:16.882
[laughter]

20:16.949 --> 20:21.219
Fee! Foo!

20:21.286 --> 20:23.288
You can't stay out here!

20:23.355 --> 20:26.058
It's too dangerous.

20:26.124 --> 20:28.226
- We've been staying out here
our entire lives,

20:28.293 --> 20:30.963
and nothing bad's
ever happened.

20:31.029 --> 20:32.831
- I'm gonna live forever!

20:32.898 --> 20:35.000
{\an1}- Hey, Foo,
let's climb above these trees

20:35.067 --> 20:37.002
{\an1}and see
who can catch the most rain.

20:37.069 --> 20:39.504
{\an3}- I'm gonna catch me
a swimming pool.

20:39.571 --> 20:45.611
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:45.677 --> 20:47.045
both: Whoa.

20:47.112 --> 20:50.148
- I'm not leaving until you guys
have a real home.

20:50.215 --> 20:53.485
- Harvey, your home
is a box,

20:53.552 --> 20:55.621
but the whole forest
is our home.

20:55.687 --> 20:59.891
- But you don't have a toilet
or a bed or a dinner table.

20:59.958 --> 21:03.595
{\an1}- It may not be your home,
but it's got everything we need.

21:03.662 --> 21:05.497
It's got plenty of space.

21:05.564 --> 21:08.133
We can make
as much noise as we want.

21:08.200 --> 21:09.768
It's got
people to take care of

21:09.835 --> 21:12.537
and people
to take care of us.

21:12.604 --> 21:16.008
You gotta understand, Harvey,
we love our home,

21:16.074 --> 21:18.443
just like you love yours.

21:20.479 --> 21:24.516
- Okay, I get it.
I just worry about you guys.

21:24.583 --> 21:26.718
{\an1}- We know, dude,
we know,

21:26.785 --> 21:28.487
{\an1}but I promise,
you don't gotta worry.

21:28.553 --> 21:29.688
We're gonna be fine.

21:29.755 --> 21:32.591
[thunder]

21:32.658 --> 21:33.925
[all scream]

21:33.992 --> 21:36.928
<i>[soothing music]</i>

21:36.995 --> 21:41.233
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.299 --> 21:43.168
Okay, how about this?

21:43.235 --> 21:44.736
We'll keep living outside,

21:44.803 --> 21:47.606
{\an1}but when it gets crazy,
we'll come stay here with you.

21:47.673 --> 21:50.409
{\an3}- That sounds
like a great plan.

21:50.475 --> 21:52.010
- Can I get a refill?

21:52.077 --> 21:56.715
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:56.782 --> 21:59.718
[all snoring]

22:01.887 --> 22:04.823
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.890 --> 22:12.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>
